def highest_edge_score_node(edges: List[int]) -> int:
    scores = [0] * len(edges)
    for i, edge in enumerate(edges):
        scores[edge] += i
    return scores.index(max(scores))
```

    1. Create an array "scores" with the same length as "edges" and fill it with zeros.
2. Iterate through the "edges" array. For each index i, increment the score array value at the position of edges[i] by i.
3. Find the index of the maximum value in the "scores" array and return it. In the case of a tie, the smallest index will be returned first, as required.

